            <div corresp="#c4257f2">
                <head>Vera Cruz, Mexico.</head>
                <p>Francis R. Stewart, Vice Consul, was appointed as Consul of ce, 8 Sept. 14, 1917
                    and turned over the office to Consul Foster Mar. 31, 1919.</p>
                <p>Maurice Brulay, V. C. de carrière, appts Consul class 7, Apr. 5, 1920; on detail
                    at Veracruz, Declined appointment as U. C. de carinère 4-29-1920.</p>
                <p>W.M. Parker Mitchell, Consul Cl. 7, lately at Dept of State, detailed to Vera
                    Cung Oct. 14, 1920; detailed to Mexico City instead of Vera Cruz Oct. 246,
                    1920</p>
                <p>John 2. lewood, Consul, Cl. 3, lately detailed to Tampico, was detailed to Vera
                    Cruz July 18, 1922 and assumed charge Sept. 16, 1922. assumed charge Sept. 16,
                    1922. assigned to Tampico Oct. 2, 1923.0</p>
